Steps
Step 1: Open Web Interface
Open browser
Type: localhost:9869
Login using:
Username: oneadmin
Password: opennebula
Step 2: Navigate to Infrastructure
Click on Infrastructure tab
Select Clusters
Choose the required cluster
Step 3: Verify Resources

Inside cluster, check:

Hosts tab → Select all hosts
Vnets tab → Select all virtual networks
Datastores tab → Select all datastores
Step 4: Add New Host
Go to Infrastructure → Hosts
Click on + (Add Host)
Enter host name
Click Create
Step 5: Select Virtual Machine
Go to Instances (VMs)
Select the VM you want to migrate
Step 6: Perform Migration
Click on Migrate option (8th icon)
Select Migrate from dropdown
Popup window appears
Choose target host
Click Migrate
Step 7: Verify Migration
Before migration: VM runs on source host
After migration: VM runs on target host
